pd_0_com_0text: Good day to you, kind sir.
pd_3_com_0text: I am! Little barky here finally returned to me after being lost for more than a week.
pd_4_com_0text: I was fearing the worst. Luckily I was wrong.
pd_5_com_0text: I wonder what happened to him.
pd_7_com_0text: Wauw, he really seams to like you.
pd_8_com_0text: I might have helped him finding his way back a little time ago.
pd_10_com_0text: You know, I once found a magic scroll. I’m not really a adventurer so I have no real need for it.
pd_16_com_0text: He was missing for more than a week.
pd_17_com_0text: Well he might turn up then. Don’t you worry.
pd_19_com_0text: Some moments earlier I saw a vulture with a dogs leg in his mount.
pd_20_com_0text: Oh dahm. Didn’t see that coming.
pd_21_com_0text: The leg had the distinct spots of Fluffy. I’m sure it was him.
pd_22_com_0text: Oh well, many stray dogs out there. Just get a new one.
pd_23_com_0text: You’re not a very emotional person, are you?
pd_25_com_0text: Can you do something for me?
pd_27_com_0text: Comment...Fluffy always played with this bone. Can you please take it from me?
pd_28_com_0text: It has some weird scriptures, a spell I think. Can’t read so…
pd_29_com_0text: Sure I will take it from you. Thanks.
pd_30_com_0text: Thanks? It is not a gift. I just don’t want it anymore.
pd_31_com_0text: Ok fine. Well, good luck pall.
